e sum of N2 million with one reasonable and reliable surety in like sum. Ibrahim adjourned the case until February 22 for hearing. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria The police on Monday arraigned a 19-year-old mechanic, Rasaq Shafiu in Abuja, for allegedly stealing handset and N5,000 cash from one Mr Emmanuel Okoli. Shafiu, who resides at Gwari village, Mpape area of Abuja, is facing a three-count charge of conspiracy, stealing and assault before a Grade I Area Court… February 24, 2020 In "Metro" An FCT High Court, Jabi on Wednesday refused to admit a security guard, Chimsom Ekenga, who allegedly raped a nine-year-old girl, at the Camp of Internally Displaced Person’s (IDP), Karamajiji, Airport Road, Abuja. April 19, 2019 In "News" The police on Tuesday docked one Ibrahim Musa in a Karmo Grade 1 Area Court, Abuja for allegedly attempting to steal 15 chickens. July 17, 2018 In "News"